250 g Ground Turkey
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 unit(s) Black Beans
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
85 g Tortilla Chips
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
200 mL Crushed Tomatoes
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.
Add tortillas to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Sprinkle cheese over top. Set aside.

Heat a large pot over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then turkey, onions and peppers.
Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Carefully drain and discard excess fat.
Add Mexican Seasoning and Zesty Garlic Blend. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Add black beans and their liquid, tomato sauce base and crushed tomatoes.
Cook, stirring often, until chili thickens slightly, 3-4 min.

Meanwhile, place baking sheet with tortilla chips in the middle of the oven. Broil until cheese has melted and chips are golden brown, 2-3 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on the chips so they don't burn!)
Divide chili between bowls. Dollop with sour cream.
Serve cheesy chips on the side for dipping.

If you've opted to get tukey, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef.